Interpretation: CHW2018 closure in the non-degenerate bridge regime
requires a \emph{distance} component (effective reduction in
\(D_M(z_*)\)), not only a sound-horizon rescaling. This is diagnostic
only; early-time closure remains deferred in v11.0.0.

Phase-2 E2 status note: these are compressed-priors diagnostics under
explicit scan families/filters. v11.0.0 does not claim a full CMB
power-spectrum or peak-level closure module. Current E2 outputs are
versioned evidence for an open early-time closure problem, while
late-time claims remain scoped independently.

\textbf{Pointers:} the referee pack includes a consolidated
\texttt{early\_time\_e2\_synthesis.md} verdict and the
\texttt{diagnostics\_index.md} module index, plus
\texttt{early\_time\_e2\_plan.md} and \texttt{early\_time\_bridge.md}
for implementation details.

\hypertarget{perturbations-and-structure-formation-bridge-diagnostic-checkpoint}{%
\subsection{10.2 Perturbations and structure-formation bridge
(diagnostic checkpoint)}\label{perturbations-and-structure-formation-bridge-diagnostic-checkpoint}}

Phase-2 now includes a compact structure bridge for reviewer-facing
diagnostics: BBKS transfer-function sampling and GR-baseline linear
growth (\(D(z)\), \(f(z)\), optional \(f\sigma_8\)) driven by explicit
background histories. This is a diagnostic approximation layer, not a
full perturbation/Boltzmann module and not a survey-level LSS fit.
Dark-matter treatment remains baseline-conservative in the current
release, while perturbation-level closure is deferred.

\textbf{Pointers:} \texttt{structure\_formation\_status.md};
\texttt{v11.0.0/scripts/phase2\_sf\_structure\_report.py}.

